	     Durban – A KwaZulu-Natal cop and a suspected accomplice have been arrested for allegedly selling police issued ammunition and weapons. Hawks spokesperson Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo said the 46-year-old warrant officer from Bayview police station in Chatsworth and his 50-year-old accomplice were nabbed following an undercover operation.  ''The Hawks Anti-Corruption Task Team 'worked' with the duo posing as criminals and managed to purchase lots of ammunition, bullet proof vests, pepper spray and police uniforms.'' Both men were arrested on Friday and will appear at the Durban Regional Court on Monday.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  